{
  "texts": [
    "Early pooling uses Eigen decomposition to perform graph coarsening operations, which is often time-consuming.",
    "The global pooling methods accomplish the pooling operation through a one-step strategy.",
    "Its main idea is to use neural networks to learn the representation of the nodes in each layer, and then aggregate the representations of each node by maximizing, averaging, or summing to get the representation of the whole graph.",
    "Global pooling methods focus on capturing the feature information of the graph but may ignore the hierarchical structure of the graph and the relationships between different nodes.",
    "Unlike global pooling, the hierarchical pooling methods adopt a layer-by-layer extraction strategy to gradually reduce the number of nodes on the graph."
  ]
}